dspace-development.title: Symplectic Elements: Missing Results for Specific Query
OAR: Missing Button for Metadata Review

comments.body:
Following a Zoom meeting with Hannah and Yuan yesterday afternoon, a number of details were identified regarding this issue, and the following steps were identified as needed to resolve this:

- Remove the `Accept/Reject/Edit Metadata Step` workflow from all Collections
- Remove the `Edit Metadata Step` from all Collections
- Create the `Accept/Reject Step` for all Collections

In response to Yuan informing me that a user, following the testing of this, was receiving e-mails, I have also created a `Submitters` workflow for all Collections, and I have migrated any existing users from the `Accept/Reject/Edit Metadata Step` into the `Accept/Reject Step` workflow.
I have requested user review for these changes, and will proceed based upon their feedback.

comments.body:
This appears to be a permissions issue on the server.  The directory should be owned by the web service user (www-data), not the deploy user.  When adjusted manually in staging to test, this resolved the issue.  

All directories under `/var/local/files` should be read/writeable by the web service user.

orangelight.title: Change advanced search facet selection to bootstrap-select for accessibility

comments.body:
[![Coverage Status](https://coveralls.io/builds/45612394/badge)](https://coveralls.io/builds/45612394)

Coverage remained the same at 96.74% when pulling **6b5468104c18b2b9a1d9f7243c566a3b23abe478 on accessible-select** into **f6ffd6bb38a10ef836fd6699cdbd43221c6a94e7 on main**.

@carolyncole I tested it on staging. The tab key announces as expected. Where I'm confused is when the screen reader goes over the 'Limit results by' for every combo box it says 'list box' then it reads the content and in the end it announces 'Type or select access types, list box pop up, Menu pop-up combobox'. I think this message should come before reading the content? Similar behaviour with the tab key.
@christinach I updated the PR to not read the select before it is opened.  I believe that makes the most sense.  I also added a feature test for advanced search.

[![Coverage Status](https://coveralls.io/builds/45619760/badge)](https://coveralls.io/builds/45619760)

Thannk you for testing @carolyncole I'll give it a try.

@carolyncole I updated the PR. When tabkey or when letting screen reader to read, it announces if the button is collapsed or expanded. When keydown 'Enter' or Space' it collapses and expands accordingly. I also added role='button' in the facets layout. I commented the other code in case we want to use .js for the role="button". I also added a feature test to show the toggle of aria-expanded attribute.
